"```sql\nSELECT COUNT(DISTINCT account.account_id)\nFROM account\nJOIN client ON account.account_id = disp.account_id\nJOIN disp ON disp.client_id = client.client_id\nJOIN district ON client.district_id = district.district_id\nWHERE account.frequency = 'POPLATEK PO OBRATU'\nAND district.A3 = 'east Bohemia';\n```\nThis SQL query counts the number of distinct accounts that have chosen the frequency 'issuance after transaction' (represented by 'POPLATEK PO OBRATU') and are located in the 'east Bohemia' region. The query joins the necessary tables using the foreign key relationships to access the required information."